<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-PACERS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HORRY SPARKS LAKERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The campaign started a tad late, and wouldn't you
know it, the debates are over, and those CNN trucks have already
packed up and left town. Is it too late for Robert Horry to declare
his candidacy?
</P>
<P>
   For sixth man of the year, if nothing else?
</P>
<P>
   It could be a hard sell in a deep field, but Horry's late push
merits at least a few ``ayes'' at the party convention.
</P>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Lakers pushed their winning streak to 14 games
Friday night, as Horry scored 14 points to help rout the Indiana
Pacers 107-92 at Staples Center.
</P>
<P>
   Horry has been the Lakers' most consistent weapon off the bench
the last three weeks, and he continued the onslaught by making his
first five shots and scrapping for several loose balls, inspiring
periodic ``Horr-rry'' chants throughout the building.
</P>
<P>
   He finished 5 for 7 from the field and added four rebounds, four
assists and a Pacer-deflating swat of an Austin Croshere layup
attempt in the fourth quarter.
</P>
<P>
   It was Horry's second-quarter work that established the tone,
though. He scored 12 points in the quarter as the Lakers cruised to
a 17-point lead by halftime and never looked back.
</P>
<P>
   The victory kept the Lakers a game and a half ahead of the
Portland Trail Blazers and extended their home winning streak to
eight games. In beating the Pacers, they avenged a January loss at
Indiana, which snapped their previous, 16-game winning streak. The
Lakers also avoided being swept in the season series, something no
team has done this season.
</P>
<P>
   And they figured out how to beat the East's best team, their
potential opponent if they reach the NBA Finals.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm always curious to see how teams will play us,'' coach Phil
Jackson said of the possible Finals preview, ``because there's a
prevailing philosophy as to how to play a team. Everybody tries a
little something different, because we basically show people the
same thing all the time.''
</P>
<P>
   In other words, they showed them a lot of Shaq and Kobe again.
Shaquille O'Neal finished with 31 points and 15 rebounds in an
abbreviated, 36-minute stint, and Bryant scored 22 points. O'Neal
struggled early, finishing 13 of 28 from the field.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers had a commanding 56-39 lead by halftime, having
established their dominance early in the first quarter and
capitalizing on 11 Pacer turnovers, converting them for 18 points.
</P>
<P>
   O'Neal scored eight points in 15-0 run that established the
initial double-digit lead, and the Lakers took a 30-16 lead into
the second quarter.
</P>
<P>
   The bench took over from there.
</P>
<P>
   After the Pacers opened the second with a 7-1 run to cut the
lead to eight, the reserves responded. A Rick Fox layup, then an
Horry 3-pointer. Then another 3 from Horry and a 3 from Brian Shaw,
a Bryant reverse jam (on an Horry feed), and an Horry turnaround
jumper, and the Lakers had a 21-point lead.
</P>
<P>
   Horry was a perfect 4 for 4 from the field and 2 for 2 from the
foul line in the second.
</P>
<P>
   O'Neal was just 6 for 18 but finished the half with 16 points
and 10 rebounds in a mere 19 minutes of work. Bryant scored 10
points.
</P>
<P>
   So the Lakers' string of wins is now just two shy of matching
their earlier 16-game streak. When the previous one ended, the
Lakers confessed to overconfidence buoyed by the streak itself. And
this time?
</P>
<P>
   ``We're not going to talk about that until it happens,'' Jackson
said, ``and when it happens we're going to try to rebound from
whatever knocks us off our pedestal.''
</P>
<P>
   This time, they might even know a little better how to stay on
that pedestal for a while longer.
</P>
<P>
   ``Perhaps, you know we might be able to do it,'' Jackson said.
``We didn't falter (in the last streak) until, really, fatigue I
think brought us more or less to an end of that buoyant streak.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-04-00 0154EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
