<P>
   BKC-RHODEN-COLUMN (New York) _ Last Sunday, the Rev. James
Forbes walked up to the pulpit at Riverside Church to deliver his
weekly sermon. Four police officers had been cleared in the
shooting of Amadou Diallo, emotions were raging and the
congregation was waiting to hear Forbes, the senior minister,
render a fiery perspective. But before he began, Forbes said he had
some housekeeping to do. Many had read or heard the church's name
mentioned in connection with an inquiry by the NCAA. Specifically,
the NCAA was investigating the role the Riverside Church basketball
program had played in helping Erick Barkley, a Riverside alumnus
and St. John's point guard, pay tuition to a prep school in Maine.
Before Forbes called attention to the Riverside Hawks in church
last Sunday, many members of the congregation may not have known
that there was a gym downstairs, or that the gym housed one of the
most prestigious basketball programs in the United States. By
William C. Rhoden.
</P>
