<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
March 5 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact
Elizabeth Ferry at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   BAYWATCH-OVERTIME (Los Angeles) _ It's not exactly ``Baywatch.''
Los Angeles County lifeguards, the models for the popular TV show,
may have been too tired to rescue swimmers last year because some
worked as much as 105 hours of overtime a month, according to a new
audit. County Auditor-Controller Alan Sasaki found lifeguards cost
the county $1.3 million in overtime and may not have been
``physically alert and mentally capable of performing.'' By Troy
Anderson. (Will move in the ``a'' national news file and in the
``n'' California news file.)
</P>
