<P>
   ELECTION _ WASHINGTON _ What a long, strange trip it's been for
Al Gore and George Bush. A year ago, both were widely expected to
stroll to their parties' presidential nominations. And indeed,
``Super Tuesday'' primary victories this week could mark the
fulfillment of their political quests. This campaign has been like
a political game of Chutes and Ladders. Unexpected reversals of
fortune raised doubts at times whether either Bush or Gore would
make it to the finish line. Even if they do, both will be different
_ some say vastly improved _ candidates, fighting on a different
battleground than the one envisioned when the race began. (Shepard,
Cox News Service). 25.
</P>
