</P>
<P>
   JUDICIAL-NOMINATIONS (Washington) _ After a four-year wait, one
of California's most controversial judges is expected to be finally
voted on this coming week in the Senate. Many conservative
Republicans oppose Richard Paez's nomination to the U.S. 9th
Circuit Court of Appeals because they say he is too liberal. But
defenders of Paez, a U.S. District Court judge in Los Angeles, deny
that. By MARK HELM. (Filed Friday.)
