<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Lewis remembers his ``Bloody Sunday'' march across the Edmund
Pettus Bridge ``like it was yesterday.'' There was a cool breeze
blowing that Sunday afternoon, on March 7. Lewis wore a beige coat.
In his back pack he carried two books, an apple, an orange and a
toothbrush.
