<P>
   BASEBALL
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS _ The Houston Astros came close to eliminating the
Atlanta Braves from the 1999 postseason, winning the first game of
the division series before losing three straight. Expectations was
supposed to be high for the Astros this year as they move into a
new ballpark, but that was before the team lost key players Mike
Hampton, Carl Everett, Derek Bell and perhaps Moises Alou. What
happened to the team that was supposed to be a serious threat for
the National League pennant? (Stinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL/NCAA
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GIBBS _ The hiring of Gary Gibbs at the University of
Georgia has gone virtually unnoticed. Gibbs has been hired to help
strengthen Georgia's defense, but much of the talk surrounding the
hiring focused on the fact that Kevin Ramsey, the former defensive
coordinator, wasn't notified of the move and had a heated argument
with head coach Jim Donnan. Through it all, however, Gibbs has
tried to remained focused on the job at hand - helping the Georgia
defense. (Towers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25. MOVED
</P>
